Junior. I&#39;m going to deemphasize connections between letters beyond a
small number of ligatures. There are several things I want from a new
font: regular, bold, italic, bold italic; both serif and sans serif
typefaces, etc. A strong desire to change the keyboard mapping was one
of the original motivators for me, actually.

I like the examples for Shavian from Kingsley Read that are in the
document Moira recently uploaded. (Thanks, Moira!) Right now I&#39;m
reading &quot;Designing Type&quot; by Karen Cheng, sketching ideas by hand, and
fiddling around with FontForge a bit. I&#39;m a scientist, not an artist,
so don&#39;t expect anything of beauty any time soon.

Ted


